about.summary: LFZip: Multivariate floating-point time series lossy compression under maximum error distortion

name: lfzip
raw_meta_yaml:
# Note: there are many handy hints in comments in this example -- remove them when you've finalized your recipe

{% set name = "LFZip" %}
{% set version = "1.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/shubhamchandak94/LFZip/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 6fa722a5756b89278966064785bc3548f969dffa00cf7929b65b245689331106

build:
  number: 0
  skip: True  # [win]

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
  host:
  run:
    - python >=3
    - numpy
    - libbsc

test:
  source_files:
      - data/evaluation_datasets/gas/HT_Sensor_dataset_combined.npy

about:
  home: https://github.com/shubhamchandak94/LFZip
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'LFZip: Multivariate floating-point time series lossy compression under maximum error distortion'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    # GitHub IDs for maintainers of the recipe.
    - ShubhamChandak94
